Sentencas: Layered-perovskite Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+delta (PBC, x = 0 - 0.30) oxides are designed and evaluated as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Evaluation of Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0-0.30) as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of x on structural, thermal and electrochemical properties has been systematically investigated.
Titulo: Evaluation of Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0-0.30) as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Analysis of X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy indicates the existence of mixed valences of Pr3+/Pr4+ and Co3+/Co4+.
Titulo: Evaluation of Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0-0.30) as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the series samples, the x = 0.10 shows the best electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Evaluation of Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0-0.30) as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity reaches as high as 600 S cm(-1) at 600 - 800 degrees C. As cathode materials for electrolyte-supported single cells, the maximum power densities at 800 degrees C are 408, 713, 732, 546 and 435 mW cm(-2) for x =0, 0.05, 0.10, 0.20 and 0.30, respectively.
Titulo: Evaluation of Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0-0.30) as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our results demonstrate that the layered-perovskite Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+delta are potential cathode materials for SOFCs, which electrochemical properties can be improved by optimizing Pr/Ba molar ratio.
Titulo: Evaluation of Pr1+xBa1-xCo2O5+δ (x=0-0.30) as cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells
